methods were transient. Cumulative life-table continuation rate per 100 women at 
four years was 0.91+/-0.02 (SE). The pregnancy failure rate was 0.04 or 4.3%. 
The results of this study indicate that intrauterine insertion of quinacrine 
pellets is a safe, acceptable and effective method of non-surgical female 
sterilization.

